[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":2020},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think\u002F":1998,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F13\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think\u002F":2007},"\u002Fhtml\u002F20230613\u002F61882704\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":17,"date":1980,"description":1981,"extension":1982,"lang":1983,"meta":1984,"navigation":79,"path":1985,"readingMinutes":1986,"seo":1987,"standalone":1988,"stem":1989,"tags":1990,"tldr":1995,"updated":1980,"url":1996,"__hash__":1997},"content\u002Fen\u002FHTML\u002Fhtml-semantics-matter-more-than-you-think.md","HTML Semantics Matter More Than You Think (And the Tags You Ignore)","4399566647",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1966},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,37,40,43,95,104,107,111,114,202,205,213,218,236,239,273,276,362,373,377,382,406,409,451,454,485,489,493,498,504,533,539,544,548,557,578,581,588,591,595,599,602,619,653,656,661,666,681,684,744,747,804,809,813,816,833,846,863,884,887,1201,1205,1215,1444,1449,1459,1463,1466,1483,1502,1505,1556,1560,1577,1585,1631,1643,1647,1650,1682,1685,1693,1785,1802,1821,1926,1929,1932,1938,1947,1959,1962],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"HTML","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fhtml-seo\u002Fisray_notarray_World_Wide_Web_a6cd202a-21ef-4dbb-996b-fdbea95b4d86.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"Let's get serious about something a lot of people overlook — HTML semantics. Ignoring this leads to bad SEO, less-readable pages, and harder maintenance down the line. Let's talk about it.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"what-does-semantic-actually-mean","What does \"semantic\" actually mean?",[12,32,33],{},"Quick warm-up — semantics in the frontend context is about whether your HTML tags match their intended purpose and meaning.",[12,35,36],{},"A bit vague? OK so what's the benefit of being semantic? You've probably heard:",[12,38,39],{},"\"Good semantics improves your SEO.\"",[12,41,42],{},"Just that? No — there's more. Quick example: if you have a heading, which tag would you use?",[44,45,50],"pre",{"className":46,"code":47,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Ch1>This is a heading\u003C\u002Fh1>\n\n\u003Cdiv>This is a heading\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n","html","",[51,52,53,74,81],"code",{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,55,58,62,66,69,71],"span",{"class":56,"line":57},"line",1,[54,59,61],{"class":60},"s8XSl","\u003C",[54,63,65],{"class":64},"syv7_","h1",[54,67,68],{"class":60},">This is a heading\u003C\u002F",[54,70,65],{"class":64},[54,72,73],{"class":60},">\n",[54,75,77],{"class":56,"line":76},2,[54,78,80],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":79},true,"\n",[54,82,84,86,89,91,93],{"class":56,"line":83},3,[54,85,61],{"class":60},[54,87,88],{"class":64},"div",[54,90,68],{"class":60},[54,92,88],{"class":64},[54,94,73],{"class":60},[12,96,97,98,100,101,103],{},"If you've been doing this a while, you'd pick ",[51,99,65],{}," immediately. But a newbie might pick ",[51,102,88],{},". Why? Because they haven't really learned what each tag is for, so they end up picking the wrong one.",[12,105,106],{},"To avoid that, let's go through what each tag actually means.",[20,108,110],{"id":109},"semantic-tags","Semantic tags",[12,112,113],{},"Heads up — HTML has a ton of tags, can't cover them all. I'll just show common examples:",[115,116,117,127,132,138,143,154,166,178],"ul",{},[118,119,120,122,123,126],"li",{},[51,121,65],{},"–",[51,124,125],{},"h6"," → Headings",[118,128,129,131],{},[51,130,12],{}," → Paragraph",[118,133,134,137],{},[51,135,136],{},"a"," → Hyperlink",[118,139,140,142],{},[51,141,15],{}," → Image",[118,144,145,147,148,147,151,153],{},[51,146,115],{},", ",[51,149,150],{},"ol",[51,152,118],{}," → Lists",[118,155,156,147,159,147,162,165],{},[51,157,158],{},"table",[51,160,161],{},"tr",[51,163,164],{},"td"," → Tables",[118,167,168,147,171,147,174,177],{},[51,169,170],{},"form",[51,172,173],{},"input",[51,175,176],{},"button"," → Forms",[118,179,180,147,183,147,186,147,189,147,192,147,195,147,198,201],{},[51,181,182],{},"header",[51,184,185],{},"footer",[51,187,188],{},"main",[51,190,191],{},"nav",[51,193,194],{},"section",[51,196,197],{},"article",[51,199,200],{},"aside"," → Page structure",[12,203,204],{},"These are the most common. Each has its own purpose, and using them correctly massively impacts SEO and readability.",[12,206,207,208,212],{},"Related — there's also the perennial debate ",[136,209,211],{"href":210},"\u002Fen\u002Fhtml\u002F2023\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fis-html-a-programming-language\u002F","Is HTML a programming language?"," if you're curious.",[214,215,217],"h3",{"id":216},"headings-h1h6","Headings (h1–h6)",[12,219,220,221,224,225,122,227,229,230,232,233,235],{},"The ",[51,222,223],{},"h"," in ",[51,226,65],{},[51,228,125],{}," stands for Heading. The number indicates importance and size. You can change the size with CSS, but the importance hierarchy is fixed — ",[51,231,65],{}," is most important, ",[51,234,125],{}," is least.",[12,237,238],{},"Semantically:",[115,240,241,246,251,256,262,268],{},[118,242,243,245],{},[51,244,65],{}," → most important heading",[118,247,248,250],{},[51,249,20],{}," → second most important",[118,252,253,255],{},[51,254,214],{}," → third",[118,257,258,261],{},[51,259,260],{},"h4"," → fourth",[118,263,264,267],{},[51,265,266],{},"h5"," → fifth",[118,269,270,272],{},[51,271,125],{}," → least important",[12,274,275],{},"Reading the tags alone tells you how important each heading is. Usage is dead simple:",[44,277,279],{"className":46,"code":278,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"\u003Ch1>This is an h1\u003C\u002Fh1>\n\u003Ch2>This is an h2\u003C\u002Fh2>\n\u003Ch3>This is an h3\u003C\u002Fh3>\n\u003Ch4>This is an h4\u003C\u002Fh4>\n\u003Ch5>This is an h5\u003C\u002Fh5>\n\u003Ch6>This is an h6\u003C\u002Fh6>\n",[51,280,281,294,307,320,334,348],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,282,283,285,287,290,292],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,284,61],{"class":60},[54,286,65],{"class":64},[54,288,289],{"class":60},">This is an h1\u003C\u002F",[54,291,65],{"class":64},[54,293,73],{"class":60},[54,295,296,298,300,303,305],{"class":56,"line":76},[54,297,61],{"class":60},[54,299,20],{"class":64},[54,301,302],{"class":60},">This is an h2\u003C\u002F",[54,304,20],{"class":64},[54,306,73],{"class":60},[54,308,309,311,313,316,318],{"class":56,"line":83},[54,310,61],{"class":60},[54,312,214],{"class":64},[54,314,315],{"class":60},">This is an h3\u003C\u002F",[54,317,214],{"class":64},[54,319,73],{"class":60},[54,321,323,325,327,330,332],{"class":56,"line":322},4,[54,324,61],{"class":60},[54,326,260],{"class":64},[54,328,329],{"class":60},">This is an h4\u003C\u002F",[54,331,260],{"class":64},[54,333,73],{"class":60},[54,335,337,339,341,344,346],{"class":56,"line":336},5,[54,338,61],{"class":60},[54,340,266],{"class":64},[54,342,343],{"class":60},">This is an h5\u003C\u002F",[54,345,266],{"class":64},[54,347,73],{"class":60},[54,349,351,353,355,358,360],{"class":56,"line":350},6,[54,352,61],{"class":60},[54,354,125],{"class":64},[54,356,357],{"class":60},">This is an h6\u003C\u002F",[54,359,125],{"class":64},[54,361,73],{"class":60},[363,364,372],"iframe",{"height":365,"style":366,"scrolling":367,"title":368,"src":369,"frameBorder":367,"loading":370,"allowTransparency":371,"allowFullScreen":371},300,"width: 100%;","no","h1~h6","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FExOVmZg?default-tab=result","lazy","true","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FExOVmZg\">\n  h1~h6\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[214,374,376],{"id":375},"paragraph-p","Paragraph (p)",[12,378,379,381],{},[51,380,12],{}," stands for Paragraph — used to wrap a block of text. The text can be a description, a story, anything. Length is arbitrary.",[12,383,384,385,388,389,392,393,395,396,398,399,401,402,405],{},"The most common use is article paragraphs. If you need a line break between paragraphs, use a second ",[51,386,387],{},"\u003Cp>"," rather than ",[51,390,391],{},"\u003Cbr>",". Each paragraph naturally ends and starts a new one. If you use ",[51,394,391],{}," everywhere, the structure becomes ambiguous and maintenance gets harder. For example, if you want to style the second paragraph specially, but you used ",[51,397,391],{}," instead of a separate ",[51,400,387],{},", you'll end up needing extra tags like ",[51,403,404],{},"\u003Cspan>"," to work around it.",[12,407,408],{},"So don't do this:",[44,410,412],{"className":46,"code":411,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"\u003Cp>\n  This is the first paragraph\n  \u003Cbr>\n  This is the second paragraph\n\u003C\u002Fp>\n",[51,413,414,422,427,437,442],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,415,416,418,420],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,417,61],{"class":60},[54,419,12],{"class":64},[54,421,73],{"class":60},[54,423,424],{"class":56,"line":76},[54,425,426],{"class":60},"  This is the first paragraph\n",[54,428,429,432,435],{"class":56,"line":83},[54,430,431],{"class":60},"  \u003C",[54,433,434],{"class":64},"br",[54,436,73],{"class":60},[54,438,439],{"class":56,"line":322},[54,440,441],{"class":60},"  This is the second paragraph\n",[54,443,444,447,449],{"class":56,"line":336},[54,445,446],{"class":60},"\u003C\u002F",[54,448,12],{"class":64},[54,450,73],{"class":60},[12,452,453],{},"Do this instead:",[44,455,457],{"className":46,"code":456,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"\u003Cp>This is the first paragraph\u003C\u002Fp>\n\u003Cp>This is the second paragraph\u003C\u002Fp>\n",[51,458,459,472],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,460,461,463,465,468,470],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,462,61],{"class":60},[54,464,12],{"class":64},[54,466,467],{"class":60},">This is the first paragraph\u003C\u002F",[54,469,12],{"class":64},[54,471,73],{"class":60},[54,473,474,476,478,481,483],{"class":56,"line":76},[54,475,61],{"class":60},[54,477,12],{"class":64},[54,479,480],{"class":60},">This is the second paragraph\u003C\u002F",[54,482,12],{"class":64},[54,484,73],{"class":60},[363,486,488],{"height":365,"style":366,"scrolling":367,"title":12,"src":487,"frameBorder":367,"loading":370,"allowTransparency":371,"allowFullScreen":371},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FRwqWVKM?default-tab=result","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FRwqWVKM\">\n  p\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[214,490,492],{"id":491},"anchor-a","Anchor (a)",[12,494,495,497],{},[51,496,136],{}," stands for Anchor — used to link to other pages, like Google → Facebook or Facebook → YouTube.",[12,499,220,500,503],{},[51,501,502],{},"href"," attribute sets the URL:",[44,505,507],{"className":46,"code":506,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\">IsRayNotArray\u003C\u002Fa>\n",[51,508,509],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,510,511,513,515,519,522,526,529,531],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,512,61],{"class":60},[54,514,136],{"class":64},[54,516,518],{"class":517},"sK3KL"," href",[54,520,521],{"class":60},"=",[54,523,525],{"class":524},"sWayO","\"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\"",[54,527,528],{"class":60},">IsRayNotArray\u003C\u002F",[54,530,136],{"class":64},[54,532,73],{"class":60},[12,534,535,536,538],{},"Pretty self-explanatory — ",[51,537,136],{}," is for links, and the content is the visible label, like \"IsRayNotArray\".",[363,540,543],{"height":365,"style":366,"scrolling":367,"title":541,"src":542,"frameBorder":367,"loading":370,"allowTransparency":371,"allowFullScreen":371},"a:link","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FwvQKdgR?default-tab=result","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FwvQKdgR\">\n  a:link\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[214,545,547],{"id":546},"image-img","Image (img)",[12,549,550,552,553,556],{},[51,551,15],{}," stands for Image — probably the simplest tag, since it only really needs one attribute: ",[51,554,555],{},"src",". That's the image URL:",[44,558,560],{"className":46,"code":559,"language":48,"meta":49,"style":49},"\u003Cimg src=\"https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com\u002Flogo.png\">\n",[51,561,562],{"__ignoreMap":49},[54,563,564,566,568,571,573,576],{"class":56,"line":57},[54,565,61],{"class":60},[54,567,15],{"class":64},[54,569,570],{"class":517}," src",[54,572,521],{"class":60},[54,574,575],{"class":524},"\"https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com\u002Flogo.png\"",[54,577,73],{"class":60},[12,579,580],{},"Translates to:",[12,582,583,584,587],{},"\"I want to display an image, the source is ",[51,585,586],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fexample.com\u002Flogo.png",", please render it.\"",[12,589,590],{},"And the browser renders it.",[363,592,594],{"height":365,"style":366,"scrolling":367,"title":15,"src":593,"frameBorder":367,"loading":370,"allowTransparency":371,"allowFullScreen":371},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FKKrdmaO?default-tab=result","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FKKrdmaO\">\n  img\u003C\u002Fa> by 